-- Steel Export Demand Stalling, Japan Steel Federation Chief Hayashida Says
-- Masumi Suga
-- 2010-07-20T04:35:48Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-20/steel-export-demand-stalling-japan-steel-federation-chief-hayashida-says.html

          
          
             Demand for steel exports from Japan
has stalled, an industry group chief said today.  
 Japan Iron and Steel Federation Chairman Eiji Hayashida is
“not optimistic” about steel demand in Asia, he said today at
a press briefing in Tokyo.  
